* ============================================================================
* mem_proof.dts - AIF-043 in-memory indexed table, end-to-end self-assert.
*
* Proves: an x64 table AND its native CDX-V64 index live entirely in RAM
* (ramfs), built with no LMDB and no files on disk, and ordered traversal
* reads back in native-index order.
* Self-contained: leads with DO mem (mount) + clean-slate remount; teardown unmounts
* and restores the x64 disk env. Run standalone: DO mem_proof  |  regression: REGRESSION RUN MEM
* Markers: MEM_T1/T2/T3 must all print .T.
* ============================================================================
SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

* self-contained activation: DO mem mounts the RAM VFS + sets DBF/INDEXES/LMDB slots
DO mem
* deterministic clean slate: drop any RAM files a prior/aborted run left, then re-activate
VDISK UNMOUNT
DO mem

FORMULA "MEM-TABLE-PROOF-BEGIN"

* --- build a throwaway x64 table in RAM ---
CREATE X64 MEMT (ID N(6), LNAME C(20))
* residency checkpoint: MEMT.dbf should appear as a RAM file (nonzero bytes)
VDISK STATUS
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH 1
REPLACE LNAME WITH "ZEBRA"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH 2
REPLACE LNAME WITH "ADAMS"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH 3
REPLACE LNAME WITH "MILLER"

* --- native CDX-V64 index, built in RAM (RUN8, no LMDB) ---
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG LNAME
REINDEX CDX
SET ORDER TAG LNAME

* --- ordered traversal proves the in-RAM index (sort: ADAMS,MILLER,ZEBRA) ---
TOP
? "MEM_T1_top_ADAMS:" + (ALLTRIM(LNAME) = "ADAMS")
SKIP
? "MEM_T2_next_MILLER:" + (ALLTRIM(LNAME) = "MILLER")
BOTTOM
? "MEM_T3_bottom_ZEBRA:" + (ALLTRIM(LNAME) = "ZEBRA")

* --- residency: table + index are RAM files, nothing on disk ---
VDISK STATUS

FORMULA "MEM-TABLE-PROOF-END"

* --- teardown: drop RAM, restore the disk environment ---
VDISK UNMOUNT
DO x64
